1
00:00:03,042 --> 00:00:06,673
Bhāgavatam
in the beginning says,

2
00:00:07,363 --> 00:00:16,406
tasyaiva hetoḥ prayateta kovido
na labhyate yad bhramatām upary adhaḥ
[SB: 1.5.18]

3
00:00:16,406 --> 00:00:20,134
Direct yourself towards that

4
00:00:20,134 --> 00:00:23,255
acquiring that,
which you can’t achieve

5
00:00:23,255 --> 00:00:25,705
in wandering the length 
and breadth of this Universe.

6
00:00:25,705 --> 00:00:28,533
[The Naked Truth | Don’t Sell Yourself Short]

7
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:33,613
What does that mean? 
That in all species of life

8
00:00:33,613 --> 00:00:37,593
there’s sensual activities:

9
00:00:37,593 --> 00:00:42,111
āhāra-nidrā-bhaya-maithunaṁ cha—

10
00:00:42,111 --> 00:00:44,075
eating, sleeping, 
sex, defense

11
00:00:44,075 --> 00:00:48,335
is not something exclusive 
to human civilization.

12
00:00:48,335 --> 00:00:54,883
So the Bhāgavatam śloka here
is one of the ten verses

13
00:00:54,883 --> 00:00:56,993
given by Nārada to Vedavyāsa.

14
00:00:56,993 --> 00:01:05,406
He’s saying, 
“Use your energy now

15
00:01:05,406 --> 00:01:10,756
for something that’s exclusive
to human society.

16
00:01:10,756 --> 00:01:15,179
If all these other possibilities 
are there in other species,

17
00:01:15,179 --> 00:01:17,945
don’t waste
your time on that.”

18
00:01:17,945 --> 00:01:22,345
Prabhupād used to be blunt 
about it quoting Ṛṣabhadev

19
00:01:22,345 --> 00:01:24,005
from the 5th Canto,

20
00:01:24,005 --> 00:01:27,041
nāyaṁ deho deha-bhājāṁ nṛloke

21
00:01:27,041 --> 00:01:31,331
kaṣṭān kāmān arhate viḍ-bhujāṁ ye
[SB: 5.5.1]

22
00:01:31,331 --> 00:01:36,027
The naked truth,
blunt and brutal.

23
00:01:36,027 --> 00:01:37,517
Ṛṣabhadev says,

24
00:01:37,517 --> 00:01:39,557
“Why try 
for the same pleasures

25
00:01:39,557 --> 00:01:43,770
that are available 
to the stool-eating pigs?”

26
00:01:46,121 --> 00:01:48,208
Saying, 
“As a human being,

27
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:50,988
is this how you should 
direct your energy?”

28
00:01:51,258 --> 00:01:52,981
We once were
in Vṛndāvan,

29
00:01:52,981 --> 00:01:55,911
and Śrīla Prabhupād
was giving a lecture.

30
00:01:55,911 --> 00:01:59,243
And, ah … [Laughing]

31
00:01:59,243 --> 00:02:03,215
He is talking 
about this verse,

32
00:02:03,215 --> 00:02:06,377
tapo divyaṁ putrakā yena sattvaṁ

33
00:02:06,377 --> 00:02:09,357
śuddhyed yasmād brahma-saukhyaṁ tv anantam
[SB: 5.5.1]

34
00:02:09,357 --> 00:02:10,877
Ṛṣabhadev telling his sons,

35
00:02:10,877 --> 00:02:13,100
“My dear boys,
don’t waste your time

36
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:14,695
on the same sort
of pleasures

37
00:02:14,695 --> 00:02:18,400
that are available to the animals, 
stool-eating pigs.

38
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:22,920
Do tapasyā, means 
to voluntarily inconvenience yourself

39
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:25,259
for the sake 
of spiritual realization.

40
00:02:25,259 --> 00:02:27,198
You have to suffer
one way or another,

41
00:02:27,198 --> 00:02:30,258
so this sort of voluntarily …
voluntary suffering

42
00:02:30,258 --> 00:02:35,952
will help you make progress
in the spiritual path.”

43
00:02:35,956 --> 00:02:39,445
Anyway,
brahma-saukhyaṁ tv anantam—

44
00:02:39,445 --> 00:02:43,014
instead of this temporary pleasure,

45
00:02:43,014 --> 00:02:47,684
yan maithunādi-gṛhamedhi-sukhaṁ hi tucchaṁ—
[SB: 7.9.45]

46
00:02:47,684 --> 00:02:49,108
same thing from Prahlād,

47
00:02:49,108 --> 00:02:51,591
[Ṛṣabhadev] is saying,
brahma-saukhyaṁ tv anantam—

48
00:02:51,591 --> 00:02:53,634
try for brahma-saukh, 
spiritual pleasure,

49
00:02:53,634 --> 00:02:57,097
which is anantam,
it’s unlimited.

50
00:02:57,097 --> 00:03:01,117
Don’t sell yourself short.

51
00:03:01,117 --> 00:03:05,462
Anyway, explaining this śloka

52
00:03:05,462 --> 00:03:09,803
he was talking about 
the so‒called “stool-eating pigs”,

53
00:03:09,814 --> 00:03:12,561
and Prabhupād said … 
[Laughing]

54
00:03:12,561 --> 00:03:14,573
said, “Not only …”

55
00:03:14,573 --> 00:03:16,905
I mean he was shocked 
as he travelled around the world,

56
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:19,079
flying on airplanes, 
visiting different countries.

57
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:23,097
He said, “Not only if they’re trying
for the same pleasures

58
00:03:23,097 --> 00:03:26,835
as the stool-eating pigs,

59
00:03:26,835 --> 00:03:30,690
but they’re
also eating them.

60
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:35,760
I have seen,
on the airplane.”

61
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:37,930
[Laughing]

62
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:42,811
And he said, “What is this called, 
pig’s intestine?”

63
00:03:42,811 --> 00:03:45,331
And one devotee, 
way in the back from England,

64
00:03:45,331 --> 00:03:48,226
smart, he goes, “Sausage.”

65
00:03:48,226 --> 00:03:51,996
And Prabhupād goes, 
“Just see, immediate answer.”

66
00:03:51,996 --> 00:03:54,893
[Laughing]

67
00:03:54,893 --> 00:03:59,134
Like, Prabhupād couldn’t for the life 
of him think of what this was.

68
00:03:59,134 --> 00:04:01,994
But that … he went,
“Sausage.”

69
00:04:01,994 --> 00:04:03,654
—Just see,
immediate answer.

70
00:04:03,654 --> 00:04:07,667
Like, you know 
what I am talking about.

71
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:11,077
As gross as this is, 
you know what I’m talking about.

72
00:04:11,077 --> 00:04:13,093
From first hand experience.

73
00:04:13,093 --> 00:04:17,064
Said, “Not only theу’re trying
for the same pleasures, but …

74
00:04:17,064 --> 00:04:18,524
dot, dot, dot …”

75
00:04:18,894 --> 00:04:24,344
Try to get that thing
that’s only available

76
00:04:24,354 --> 00:04:27,204
in human society—
that’s the point.

77
00:04:27,227 --> 00:04:33,040
What is that that’s 
exclusive to human beings.

78
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:35,734
athāto brahma-jijñāsā
[Vedānta-sūtra: 1.1.1]

79
00:04:35,734 --> 00:04:37,895
spiritual inquiry,

80
00:04:37,895 --> 00:04:41,035
beyond the base necessities
of existence,

81
00:04:41,035 --> 00:04:42,665
internal culture.

82
00:04:42,915 --> 00:04:49,216
Love beyond body connection.

